    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Mundis munda omnia:
    						solidis singula salubria.
    					</marginalia_text>
    					<X-ref book_title="Bible" language="LA" person="Paul" text="Omnia munda mundis"/>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				"All things are pure to pure men."			
    				Healthy things are individual to unyielding men.	 				
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
    		
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position book_orientation="90" place="left_margin">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						{ Saluberrima totius corporis, singularumq[ue] partium integritas seriò curanda: cum 
    						internis, externisq[ue] omnibus incorruptis, et exquisitè mundis: in primis dia[e]ta,
    						exercitatio, euacuatio, vestitus, stragula, aer: maximeq[ue] animi affectus.
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				{ The most healthy integrity of the whole body and its individual parts must earnestly be provided for, with
    				all things internal and external uncorrupted and exquisitely pure: first through diet, then exercise,
    				purging, clothing, bedding, air, above all in the disposition of the mind.
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
         		
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position book_orientation="270" place="right_margin">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Nihil habetur quod non habituatur: et optima dicendi, agendiq[ue] assuetudo
    						maxima est perfectionis causa. Egregium nihil sine egregia Exercitatione. 
    					</marginalia_text>
    					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				Nothing is brought into condition what may not be brought into condition: and the very best habit of saying and acting is the cause of perfection.
    				Nothing is exceptional without exceptional exercise.
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
        
